<br>
if you wanna know what difference 40 atk makes, try getting CoP from a 60 ranger.....can you feel and see it? i can, almost instantly....and i've got it free on a weapon as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
as for warrior epic, the red blades proc actually is a guaranteed 500 pt. hate list increase plus 100 dmg (if it lands of course). that may or may not be more than a SoD, i don't know, but if karthunk says it taunts good then i assume it's true. offhand damage is pretty minimal anyway (where he's prolly using it) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umegillagerilla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Megilla Gerilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 1:07:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> hum, i use 15/20 and 13/17, grats RB in staying in a bag forever. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uheka01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heka01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 2:41:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> Bonechiller isnt much of a taunter, I use one and have no problems evading. I only bag it if it's proc is getting resisted and so swap in something else (dragonrib club or silver whip of rage usually). CT is a different matter as the proc tends to blow roots loose and this annoys the chanter or shammy.<br>
<br>
I finally bagged my RB when I got Trinket of Speed, but I carry it always for situational use. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utarskinroefod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TarskinRoefod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 5:35:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> I agree with the opinions posted here, after you get 36+ % Haste and Primal you can think about bag'ing your Ragebringer if you have a good ~1.40+ (delay/dmg) weapon. If you're interested i did some parsings on soulbinder (who is known to have fairly high dmg mitigation).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.will2power.dk/roe/Comparison.html">www.will2power.dk/roe/Comparison.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I'll update it with 41% haste later...<br>
<br>
Of course this is by no means very accurate and backstab isnt being used, probably around 5 % uncertainty or more. I just did it to get a rough idea. Notice that the Main:Primal Offhand: Ragebringer performs surprisingly well. In fact so well, you would have to Main: Vyemms Fang or better and Offhand: Primal to be sure you're doing more damage.<br>
<br>
Roefod Koefod<br>
&lt;Enshadowed&gt;<br>
Brell Serilis <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utarskinroefod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TarskinRoefod</A> at: 4/9/02 5:46:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvenvensilentdagger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Venven Silentdagger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 6:44:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> &quot; because delay doesn't matter in offhand. &quot;<br>
<br>
Uhm, hi! yes it does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uemodius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 7:11:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> "most rogues bag the RB when they get primal, which then goes in offhand"<br>
<br>
Call me silly, but "bagging" an item usually involves... I dunno... a BAG. <br>
<br>
Because it is a haste item too, the new weapon needs to make up for the stats AND the resulting switch in of a new haste item in a slot previously taken up by a probably better item. <br>
<br>
Also, the warrior epic IS difficult, but lets be honest, it's just not that good, and people with them bag them all the time for better. It's a combo of both reasons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uraiid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raiid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 7:58:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> All that really matters offhand is ratio, delay means something between jack, and @#%$.<br>
<br>
I still think you should be able to slap RB in the range slot and then we could end all this discussion :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uviscerspineshank.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Viscer Spineshank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 9:41:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> I don't have any of the higher end piercers....nor do I have an alt haste item.....but what I consistantly parsed out.....Rage in mainhand, primal in offhand has consistantly scored better for me than Primal in main and rage in off.<br>
<br>
Not by much.....but if your counting......any little bit counts.<br>
<br>
If I got a better piercer, like 14/18 or 15/20.....I probably would switch.<br>
<br>
Also, I am all about ATK.  I will give up Hps, AC, other stats, other saves etc.....for ATK.  My primary job is to do damage....no other reason for my existance in fights.....whats the best way to do that?  The weapon your using, how fast your using it (haste, dly, AA points) and Your ATK. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udsarmageddon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DSArmageddon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 12:11:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> I did some tests myself with Primal/RB on a soulbinder to find out which was better in main hand.  I did it differently trying to simulate a raid situation, as that's when DPS really counts.  I kept Avatar, CoP, STR of Nature, Shiss/VoG on throughout the tests.  I found out a few things:<br>
<br>
VoG &gt; Shiss<br>
RB main = Primal main if you don't use backstab<br>
RB main &gt; Primal main if you do use backstab.  I was sitting near 1450 atk and consistantly getting 553 backstabs.<br>
<br>
Unfortunatly I don't have the parses to 'prove' it too you, partly cuz my parsing program dosn't make neet graphs and tables, mostly cuz I don't have anywhere to host it.<br>
<br>
--Demonspawn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uviscerspineshank.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Viscer Spineshank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 1:49:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=27>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> /nod Demon<br>
<br>
That is exactly what I parse.  I also like VoG over shiss.....any day.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usirigudernesskat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siri Gudernesskat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 2:41:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10643.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How good does it have to be to bag your RB?</span><hr size=1> ATM I use RB secondary, and primary I switch between Primal and Vyemm's Fang.  I don't have a good range item (Goranga Idol believe it or not haha), so I have to do a 3-way switch between Primal, Fang, and Idol (Fang's in range when Primal's in primary) after Avatar.<br>
<br>
If I didn't have Vyemm's Fang (or if I was willing to use it purely as a Range item), I would put Primal in secondary.  After Avatar, I see more 553 backstabs with RB than 479 backstabs with Primal/Fang.  I don't know why, but that's my experience.  I still use Fang over RB in primary though because of its lucidrous speed.<br>
<br>
